race.description: Lj Hooker Property Specialists Gawler Handicap
race.comment: EMPIRE GRACE (3) backs up quickly after chasing gamely into the placings at Strathalbyn. Drops back to a winning trip and is drawn advantage for gun hoop in Toeroek. Leading player. MISLUDI (7) caught the eye last start at headquarters when flashing home to just miss the frame. The form around her stacks up strongly. Big chance to strike through if she can take closer order from the low draw this time. GLOBAL TURN (1) is another who likes to do her best work late. Likely to drift back again from the draw but gets in well with the claim and just needs the gaps to burst through again. Don't take lightly. CHILLCUZ (4) couldn't go on with the job last start at Murray Bridge when sent forward. Expect them to be a fraction more conservative this time but should still land handy from the draw. Can't leave out. PRESS EXPRESS (8) doesn't know how to run a bad race and is always worth including.
